text: Pamplona Cathedral is a famous Roman catholic cathedral in Spain. It is the seat of archdiocese of Pamplona, Spain. It is famous for its Gothic architecture. ==Bibliography== *Navallas, Arturo; Jusué, Carmen (eds.): La catedral de Pamplona (2 vols.), Pamplona: Caja de Ahorros de Navarra, 1994 *Arraiza, Jesús: Catedral de Pamplona: la otra historia, Pamplona: Ediciones y Libros, 1994 ==Other websites== * Cathedral of Pamplona's web page Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:Pamplona Category:14th- century buildings and structures
